Past/Present: CLI - use ssh or telnet to get to do device & manually configure the device with commands

- Only difference between SSH & Telnet is SSH uses encryption
- SSH uses TCP

Present: NETCONF (2006) - a protocol for network configuration

Additional things came out of NETCONF - for intsance, YANG data model

The idea was to replace SNMP with NETCONF by sending structured data (XML) to & from client

Transport mechanism sits on top of SSH, can even use port 22
